{"key":"processedPost-6053720","value":{"id":6053720,"first":6053652,"last":6053720,"when":1158093864,"utime":"09/12/06 11:44 PM","content":"I would go half and half with the manure/coir.  Lay the cow manure out in the sun for a few days so the ammonia can flash off before using.  I would also use five to ten percent gypsum in the compost mix, as well as up to five percent calcium carbonate if you have it, or half a teaspoon of hydrated lime per cup of manure/coir.  The mixture will have a PH of around 5, so you want to add something to buffer it.<br />RR","title":"Re: bulk substrate recipe","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}